This paper is primarily focused on the limitations of CNNs in recognizing negative images, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of current training methods, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of semantic adversarial examples is introduced, which is a topic of interest in both computer vision and machine learning. Additionally, the paper discusses the classification of images, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and neural networks (cs.NE).
